es, for which the distribution of\nfertilities has an infinite variance, we find p_r(r)~1/r^(1+1/gamma) and\np_g(g)~1/g^(1+1/(gamma -1)). These predictions are checked by numerical\nsimulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 May 2003 00:25:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 19 Mar 2004 19:32:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
